OL,6,F"I want the old (me) back. I don't
OL,7,Fthink she will ever come back. She's
OL,8,Fgone.
OL,10,F"I always think of others before
OL,11,Fmyself. This should not have happened
OL,12,Fto anyone but rather it had been me
OL,13,Fthan a 90-year-old woman who would
OL,14,Fnever recover or a child with their
OL,15,Flife ahead of them."
OL,17,FShe added: "My greatest wish is that
OL,18,Fno-one else will ever have to go
OL,19,Fthrough the trauma (but) I promise you
OL,20,Fnow I will rise like a phoenix."
