OL,6,FMullen will serve a minimum term of
OL,7,Fseven years imprisonment before he can
OL,8,Fbe considered for parole. He will
OL,9,Fremain on licence for the rest of his
OL,10,Flife.
OL,12,FSimon Killeen, defending, said Mullen
OL,13,Fis "disgusted and ashamed" by his
OL,14,Fconduct that night which was fuelled
OL,15,Fby alcohol and drugs.
OL,17,FThe judge, His Honour Rhys Rowlands,
OL,18,Fcalled it "a brutal assault". He
OL,19,Fadded: "I'm satisfied that the risk
OL,20,Fyou pose is likely to continue sadly
OL,21,Flong into the future."
